", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-15", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "[7. Summary of the Materialist Conception of History]", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-16", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "[8. The Inconsistency of the Idealist Conception of History in General, and of German Post-Hegelian Philosophy in Particular]", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-17", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "Feuerbach: Philosophic, and Real, Liberation", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-18", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "[II. 1. Preconditions of the Real Liberation of Man]", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-19", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "[2. Feuerbach's Contemplative and Inconsistent Materialism]", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-20", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "Ruling Class and Ruling Ideas", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-21", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h4", "text": "C. The Real Basis of Ideology", "level": 4, "id": "ME5-8-22", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "Division of Labour: Town and Country", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-23", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "[2. The Division of Material and Mental Labour. Separation of Town and Country, The Guild System]", "level": 5, "id": "ME5-8-24", "source_file": "MECW05-008.html", "chapter_number": 8, "filename": "MECW05-008.html"}, {"tag": "h5", "text": "Further Division of Labour", "level": 5, "id":